  "prompt": "How long does it take for ice also known as meth to get out of your system if you have been shooting it?",
  "response": "The detection time for methamphetamine, also known as meth or ice, can vary depending on several factors including the amount used, frequency of use, metabolism, and overall health. Generally, methamphetamine can be detected in different parts of the body for the following durations:\n\n1. **Blood**: Methamphetamine is detectable in the blood for up to 1-3 days after use.\n2. **Urine**: Methamphetamine can be detected in urine for up to 3-7 days after use.\n3. **Saliva**: Methamphetamine is detectable in saliva for up to 1-4 days after use.\n4. **Hair**: Methamphetamine can be detected in hair follicles for up to 90 days or longer, depending on hair length and frequency of use.\n\nPlease note that these are general guidelines and individual differences can affect detection times. For those seeking to detox from methamphetamine, the process can vary but may often take several days to weeks for the body to fully cleanse itself from the substance. Additionally, if you are concerned about methamphetamine use or its effects, it is advisable to seek professional medical guidance and support.",
